author: Paul Vieira
title: Canada GDP Expanded 0.3% in July
text:
OTTAWA—The Canadian economy expanded for a second straight month in July, shrugging off a downturn in the first two quarters of the year caused by slumping commodity prices.
Growth in July was fueled by strength in energy production and manufacturing, and gains in the services sector, which makes up roughly two-thirds of Canada’s economic output.
